2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"cloud-computing-and-its-impact-in-the-financial-services-sector\"><\/span><strong>Cloud Computing and Its Impact in the Financial Services Sector<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>According to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pcmag.com\/news\/what-is-cloud-computing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">PCMag<\/a>, cloud computing refers to the process of storing and accessing information and software applications over the internet instead of a typical PC drive. The main distinction here is that cloud computing isn\u2019t a hard drive.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business owners prefer cloud computing as it allows them to easily access their important business information from any location and at any time. All your workers need is a working internet connection.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Presently, there are three primary types of cloud computing service models. These are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Platform as a Service (Paas): Businesses get to rent network capacity, hardware, storage, and operating systems from IaaS providers. They also need to lease application environments and software servers. Essentially, it\u2019s a cross between Iaas and Saas.<br>\u2022 Infrastructure as a Service (Iaas): Small businesses are required to rent or buy disk space and computer processing power from an external provider. You get to access the <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-do-passwordless-payments-work-are-the-safe\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"140\">payment processing<\/a> framework via the internet or a private network.<br>\u2022 Software as a Service (Saas): It\u2019s the most common type of cloud computing used by small enterprises. Users can access software applications hosted on the internet using a standard browser instead of a regular application.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Looking at the service models above, it\u2019s easy to see why businesses in all sectors, including the financial services sector, are increasingly shifting their operations to the cloud.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"guide-to-corporate-cloud-banking-for-startups\"><\/span><strong>Guide to Corporate Cloud Banking for Startups<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Startup Fintech companies are slowly disrupting the sedate world of corporate banking. Small businesses in the financial services sector are doing everything they can to keep up with their larger counterparts as they expand their operations.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>They are doing this by leveraging the technologies in use by established organizations and by modernizing their operations. Typical efforts include increased reliance on data in decision making and a gradual shift of their operations to the cloud.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Although almost all businesses are making similar moves, those facilitating internet-based financial transactions have different requirements than their counterparts. They need to address existing challenges for their customers to trust their platforms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Small businesses need to keep pace with ever-changing customer desires. Additionally, the market conditions are increasingly driving the need for these startups to provide scalable and more flexible options.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>They have to maintain scalability when developing, installing, maintaining, and updating software applications. Cloud computing helps them achieve this and ensures the flexibility of the end product.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cloud computing provides them with lower delivery path costs compared to standard on-premises models. It enables them to meet the demand for responsive and bespoke data-rich applications.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Guide-to-Corporate-Cloud-Banking-for-Startups.jpg\" alt=\"businesses\" class=\"wp-image-424\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Guide-to-Corporate-Cloud-Banking-for-Startups.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Guide-to-Corporate-Cloud-Banking-for-Startups-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/Guide-to-Corporate-Cloud-Banking-for-Startups-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"payment-processing-businesses-and-cloud-computing-its-benefits\"><\/span><strong>Payment Processing Businesses and Cloud Computing\u2014Its Benefits<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Cloud computing has many benefits to offer to a startup. It enables the entrepreneur to set up a virtual office that provides them with the flexibility needed to connect to their business at any time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It simplifies access to financial transaction information, which you can quickly access using any web-enabled device. Other <a href=\"https:\/\/www.business.qld.gov.au\/running-business\/it\/cloud-computing\/benefits\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">benefits of cloud computing<\/a> for business owners include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Access to automatic updates: Your business system will receive automated software updates depending on the contract signed with the cloud computing service provider. Such updates can include updates to computer processing power and up-to-date versions of the online payment applications.<br>\u2022 Reduced IT costs: Shifting the <strong>payment processing services<\/strong> to the cloud can significantly reduce the costs of managing the company systems. Instead of purchasing costly equipment and financial transaction systems, you can minimize expenses by relying on the resources provided by a cloud computing service provider. You will get to reduce costs because:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2601 Cloud computing has fewer time delays.<br>\u2601 The cost of new software, hardware, and system upgrades will be included in the service contract.<br>\u2601 You are likely to reduce your energy consumption.<br>\u2601 You don\u2019t have to spend money on salaries and wages for expert staff.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Flexibility of work practices: Shifting operations to the cloud allows your personnel to work from any location. They can connect to the virtual office from home, during their daily commute, or even when on holiday.<br>\u2022 Business continuity: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.business.qld.gov.au\/running-business\/protecting-business\/risk-management\/continuity-planning\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Business continuity planning<\/a> calls for small business owners to take measures that can help them to protect their business information and systems. Storing the data in the cloud allows you to resume operations quickly, even after getting affected by a power failure or natural disaster.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Risk of Cloud Computing Services to Online Payment Processors<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><br>Although <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/corporate-cloud-banking-and-strategic-growth\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"130\">cloud computing<\/a> does provide many benefits to companies offering financial services, it also comes with its share of risks. Before shifting your operations to the cloud, there\u2019s a need to understand these risks and what they will likely mean to your business.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Experts recommend undertaking a risk assessment process beforehand. Pertinent issues that you should consider include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Legislation and regulation, especially when using a service provider located abroad<br>\u2022 Privacy and service level agreements<br>\u2022 Location of your business data<br>\u2022 Security and data protection<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"why-do-small-businesses-in-the-financial-services-sector-have-a-higher-risk-profile\"><\/span><strong>Why Do Small Businesses in the Financial Services Sector Have a Higher Risk Profile?<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A vital factor to note is that the stakes for payment processing companies are much higher when moving operations to the cloud. The business and the financial transactions they support act as a bedrock for local and international economies.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Keeping in mind that their applications are distributed across numerous systems and data sets, they need to confirm their scalability and data latency. Any data fed to the payment processing platform needs to be credible at all times.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>From secure data storage to hosting applications, the cloud is everywhere. Small businesses use cloud-related services to deliver software on-demand, store and backup files, and access email. As the internet continues to change how businesses conduct their operations, it\u2019s becoming necessary for owners to learn how to use the cloud for online payments. To understand [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":423,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[23,16,14],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/365"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=365"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/365\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":425,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/365\/revisions\/425"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/423"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/